story.title: Dead Air - Episode 6
story.storyDescription: Halfway through a seven-hour flight to Paris, a woman wakes up to find everyone on the plane is dead except for her…
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Travis Pennington is a writer, literary agent, graphic artist, and leader of a crazy pack of canines. He loves ice cream because it’s cheaper than therapy, and he’s probably the most talented horror binge watcher you’ll ever find.

story.prePaywallNotification: Why was Chrissy’s brother FILMING her in her bedroom?! Keep reading DEAD AIR.
story.postPaywallNotification: What shocking image does someone slip under the cockpit door to Chrissy? Keep reading DEAD AIR.

messages.text: I can explain, but first we need to get you on the ground.
Trust me, you’ll understand everything in a few hours.
What explanation could you possibly have for spying on me in my bedroom?
I mean, REALLY?? You’re my brother for chrissake.
And this is what you do?
You should know it isn’t true.
And don’t give me some line about imagining things.
You’re on a plane full of dead people.
You heard your dead mother’s voice from the lavatory.
You saw yourself on the news as a suspected bomber.
Then why would they seem so real to you?
Maybe someone is playing the ultimate mind game on you.
I could maybe understand someone doing this to a billionaire or the First Lady.
Maybe you just don’t know WHO you really are yet.
Anyone capable of killing everyone aboard a plane and leaving only one person alive can certainly alter a video.
So how about trusting me a little?
But there’s something I need to do first.
I think we should discuss everything you plan on doing first.
I forced open the lavatory door…
The one where I heard my mother’s voice.
There was a speaker hooked up to an iPhone.
It’s like someone was pretending to be my mother.
Talking to me about the past.
Okay let’s not worry about that right now.
We need to focus on getting you on the ground first.
Then we can figure everything else out.
Can you get to the cockpit?
I’m on my way there now.
There’s a family in business class.
A mother and father and a little girl.
I could swear I saw them move.
But now she’s just staring at me.
Stay focused on getting to the cockpit.
It’s just a few feet away.
It’s coming from inside the cockpit.
A little girl is singing in the cockpit.
“Here we go round the mulberry bush”…
Have you tried talking to her?
Someone just slipped something under the door.
I don’t think I can do this anymore.
I can’t take another second of this.
She told me she had something for me.
She told me to pick up the paper on the floor.
She was naked and all cut open.
And now the little girl is singing again.
“Here we go round the mulberry bush.”
And she’s giggling at the end of every verse.
Okay, try to block out her voice.
I know it’s difficult, but you can’t give up.
There should be a phone near the door.
The flight attendants use it to talk to the captain.
Pick it up and ask if anyone can hear you.
I ran up the stairs leading to first class.
She said she had something else for me.
Hundreds crawled out from under the door.
Now I’m standing by the curtains to the first-class cabin.
But I’m afraid to pull them back.
Chrissy ignores John and opens the curtains.
They were coming up the stairs.
And the little girl was singing the entire time…
“Here we go round the mulberry bush.”
She kept telling me that I killed him.
"You killed your father. You killed your father."
The fire ants were almost at my feet and I was almost choking.
I was sitting up here in first class.
A lady is talking to me now.
I just told her what’s happening downstairs.
But she said she came from downstairs a few minutes ago…
And everything’s normal in the plane.
She said the plane has started its descent into Paris…
And I need to return to my seat or she’ll have to report an unruly passenger.
You can put your phone away now.
You’re not going to need it anymore.
Why won’t I need my phone??
Look over your shoulder and everything will be clear.
Because I’m sitting right behind you.
